org.jdesktop.core.animation.timing.evaluators
Class KnownEvaluators

java.lang.Object
  org.jdesktop.core.animation.timing.evaluators.KnownEvaluators

@Singleton
public final class KnownEvaluators
extends java.lang.Object

Manages a set of known immutable evaluator implementations that the program can find by the type they work with.

This maintains a clean separation between the core of the Timing Framework and the Swing and SWT portions by using reflection to attempt to load the non-core evaluators.

Author:
Tim Halloran

public void register(Evaluator<?> singleton)
Registers an immutable evaluator as known. The single instance passed to this method is shared by all requesters.

Parameters:
singleton - an immutable evaluator instance.

unregister

public void unregister(Evaluator<?> singleton)
Unregisters an immutable evaluator, making it unknown. Has no effect if the passed instance was not previously registered.

Parameters:
singleton - an immutable evaluator instance.

getEvaluatorFor

public <T> Evaluator<T> getEvaluatorFor(java.lang.Class<T> type)
Gets the evaluator for the passed type. This class only registers immutable evaluator implementations so multiple requests for the same type will share the same evaluator.

Type Parameters:
T - a type for which an evaluator is requested.
Parameters:
type - the Class object for T.
Returns:
an evaluator for T.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if no evaluator is registered for T.
